## 📖 Overview

Hostel operations involve multiple roles — students, wardens, and admins — each of whom should see and touch different data. Rather than trusting the frontend to hide the wrong buttons, this system encodes the permission model directly into the database so it can't be bypassed.

## ✨ Key Features

- 🔐 **Three-role permission matrix** (student / warden / admin) enforced via **Supabase Row Level Security (RLS)** — access control lives in the database, not just the UI
- 📊 **Interactive analytics dashboard** for wardens — occupancy, complaints, and activity at a glance
- 🧑‍🎓 Student-facing portal for room details, complaints, and requests
- 🛡️ Zero data leakage between roles by design, not by convention

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
┌───────────────────┐
│  React + TypeScript │
│      Frontend        │
└──────────┬──────────┘
           ▼
    ┌──────────────┐
    │   Supabase    │
    │  Auth + RLS    │  ◄── permission matrix enforced here
    └──────────────┘
```

## 🧰 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React, TypeScript |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS |
| Backend / Auth / DB | Supabase (PostgreSQL + RLS) |

## 🚀 Getting Started

```bash
git clone https://github.com/hackerstudent29/MSAJCE-LORIN.git
cd MSAJCE-LORIN

npm install
npm run dev
```

Set your Supabase credentials in `.env`:
```
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_project_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key
```

